{"article_id":"VUnHmSaQ46UfVYnq","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"President Obama ' s \" red line \" vow of action against Syria turned a lighter shade of pink Thursday ,","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"with Secretary of State John F. Kerry saying","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"a U.S. military strike \" might \" be necessary","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"if talks","depth":10},{"id":4,"text":"led by Russia","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"fail to compel Syria to turn over its chemical weapons .","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"As negotiators met in Switzerland on the unfolding crisis ,","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"Mr. Kerry appeared to concede the diplomatic reins to the Russians ,","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"who are insisting","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"that the U.S. withdraw its threat of missile strikes","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"before the regime of Syrian President Bashar Assad agrees to give up its chemical weapons stockpile .","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"\" President Obama has made clear","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"that ,","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"should diplomacy fail ,","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"force might be necessary","depth":12},{"id":15,"text":"to deter and degrade Assad ' s capacity","depth":13},{"id":16,"text":"to deliver these weapons , \"","depth":13},{"id":17,"text":"Mr. Kerry said in Geneva after a meeting with Russian Foreign Minister Sergey Lavrov .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"His comment offered less certainty","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"than President Obama had of a missile strike .","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"Mr. Obama said Tuesday","depth":5},{"id":21,"text":"that he was keeping U.S. forces in the region \" in a position","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"to respond","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"if diplomacy fails. \"","depth":6},{"id":24,"text":"Asked about Mr. Kerry ' s remark ,","depth":5},{"id":25,"text":"the White House said","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"the secretary of state had not misspoken .","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"\" I think","depth":6},{"id":28,"text":"that that allows for ,","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"you know ,","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"a variety of things","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"that could happen in the next days and weeks","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"with regard to this matter , \"","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"said White House press secretary Jay Carney ,","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"adding","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"that \" a military option is important to maintain . \"","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"Events in the Syria crisis continued to develop at a fast-moving clip Thursday ,","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"with much of the action happening far from the White House .","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"Russian President Vladimir Putin ,","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"after penning a New York Times op-ed","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"panning the U.S. approach to the Syrian crisis and the idea of American \" exceptionalism , \"","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"pushed forward with his own plan","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"for resolving the crisis .","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"In New York , Syria ' s U.N . Ambassador Bashar Ja ' afari told reporters","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"that he had formally presented to U.N. Secretary-General Ban Ki-moon his country ' s application","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"to join the Chemical Weapons Convention as a first step","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"to putting the regime ' s stockpiles under international control .","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"SEE ALSO :","depth":6},{"id":48,"text":"Russia aims to hide its role","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"in stockpiling Syria ' s arsenal :","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"Rogers","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"In Damascus , Mr. Assad announced","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"that he had signed the papers","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"putting the treaty accession into motion","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"while pointedly noting","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"that he was responding to Moscow ' s offer and not to the threats from Washington .","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"Mr. Kerry ' s comments in Geneva signaled a further downsizing of Mr. Obama ' s original vow","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"to punish the Syrian regime for an Aug. 21 sarin gas attack","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"that","depth":13},{"id":59,"text":"the U.S. said","depth":13},{"id":60,"text":"killed 1,429 people near Damascus .","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"Mr. Obama had been saying for a year","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"that such an atrocity","depth":14},{"id":63,"text":"using Syria ' s known chemical weapons","depth":14},{"id":64,"text":"would cross a \" red line \"","depth":13},{"id":65,"text":"requiring a tough U.S. response .","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"On Aug. 31 , Mr. Obama said","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"he had decided to launch a \" limited \" attack on Syria","depth":14},{"id":68,"text":"to prevent it from using chemical weapons again ,","depth":14},{"id":69,"text":"but he would wait for Congress to vote on the use of military force .","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"A few days later , Mr. Obama said","depth":12},{"id":71,"text":"he hadn ' t created the \" red line \"","depth":14},{"id":72,"text":"but the international community had ,","depth":14},{"id":73,"text":"and therefore his credibility was not at stake .","depth":13},{"id":74,"text":"On Monday , Russia seized on an offhand remark from Mr. Kerry","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"to float its own deal through the United Nations","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"to avoid a U.S. strike against Syria .","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"On Tuesday , Mr. Obama asked Congress to hold off a vote indefinitely on military action","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"while he pursued the diplomatic course .","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"Mr. Kerry Thursday tried to lay down new conditions","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"before Washington would agree to any deal between Mr. Putin and Mr. Assad .","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"\" This is not a game , \"","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"Mr. Kerry said .","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"\" It has to be real .","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"It has to be comprehensive .","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"It has to be verifiable .","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"It has to be credible .","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"It has to be timely","depth":14},{"id":88,"text":"and implemented in a timely fashion .","depth":14},{"id":89,"text":"And finally , there ought to be consequences","depth":14},{"id":90,"text":"if it doesn ' t take place . \"","depth":14},{"id":91,"text":"Mr. Lavrov called for rules","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"under which Syria would join the Chemical Weapons Convention","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"and said","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"a solution \" will make unnecessary \" a military strike on Syria .","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"But Mr. Assad told the Russian TV interviewer","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"that he would agree to turn over Syria ' s chemical weapons","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"only if the U.S. drops its threat of attack .","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"\" This does not mean that Syria will sign these documents ,","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"carry out the conditions","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"and that ' s it , \"","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"Mr. Assad said .","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"\" This bilateral process is based , first of all , on the United States stopping its policy","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"of threatening Syria . \"","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"Mr. Obama and his aides kept up his tit-for-tat exchange of insults with Mr. Putin .","depth":5},{"id":105,"text":"Responding to the Russian leader ' s New York Times op-ed","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"that belittled Mr. Obama ' s claim of \" American exceptionalism , \"","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"the White House shot back at the lack of openness in Russian society .","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"\" Russia offers a stark contrast","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"that demonstrates","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"why America is exceptional , \"","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"said White House press secretary Jay Carney .","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"\" Unlike Russia , the United States stands up for democratic values and human rights in our own country and around the world . \"","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"Mr. Carney said","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"Mr. Putin enjoyed a freedom of expression in his op-ed","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"that the Russian government does not tolerate from its own citizens .","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"\" There ' s a great irony ... in the placement of an op-ed like this","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"because it reflects the truly exceptional tradition in this country of freedom of expression , \"","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"Mr. Carney said .","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"\" And that is not a tradition","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"shared in Russia , by Russia .","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"Freedom of expression has been on the decrease over the past dozen or so years in Russia . \"","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"The disrespectful rhetoric seemed like an inauspicious foundation for a diplomatic solution to Syria ,","depth":6},{"id":123,"text":"and Mr. Obama ' s aides said","depth":7},{"id":124,"text":"they remained skeptical","depth":8},{"id":125,"text":"that the talks would produce results .","depth":8},{"id":126,"text":"But Mr. Kerry said in Geneva","depth":7},{"id":127,"text":"that diplomacy was \" clearly preferable to military action . \"","depth":7},{"id":128,"text":"Mr. Kerry said","depth":8},{"id":129,"text":"the U.S. is \" serious about engaging in substantive , meaningful negotiations","depth":9},{"id":130,"text":"even as our military maintains its current posture","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"to keep up the pressure on the Assad regime. \"","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"He said","depth":9},{"id":133,"text":"the Russian proposal is an \" immense \" challenge .","depth":9},{"id":134,"text":"\" It ' s too early to tell","depth":11},{"id":135,"text":"whether these efforts will succeed , \"","depth":11},{"id":136,"text":"he said .","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"\" The technical challenges","depth":12},{"id":138,"text":"of trying to do this in the context of a civil war","depth":12},{"id":139,"text":"are obviously immense .","depth":11},{"id":140,"text":"But","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"despite how difficult this is ,","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"with the collaboration of our experts","depth":14},{"id":143,"text":"- and only with the compliance of the Assad regime -","depth":14},{"id":144,"text":"we do believe","depth":13},{"id":145,"text":"there is a way","depth":13},{"id":146,"text":"to get this done . \"","depth":13},{"id":147,"text":"In his op-ed , Mr. Putin chided Mr. Obama","depth":4},{"id":148,"text":"for threatening military action ,","depth":4},{"id":149,"text":"writing ,","depth":4},{"id":150,"text":"\" We must stop using the language of force . \"","depth":4},{"id":151,"text":"But Mr. Kerry said","depth":4},{"id":152,"text":"the threat of a U.S. attack brought Russia and Syria to the bargaining table .","depth":4},{"id":153,"text":"\" Only the credible threat of force","depth":6},{"id":154,"text":"- and the intervention of President Putin and Russia","depth":7},{"id":155,"text":"based on that -","depth":7},{"id":156,"text":"has brought the Assad regime to acknowledge for the first time","depth":6},{"id":157,"text":"that it even has chemical weapons , \"","depth":6},{"id":158,"text":"he said .","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":317,"left":305,"right":316,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":305,"left":194,"right":304,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":194,"left":182,"right":193,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":182,"left":178,"right":181,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":178,"left":164,"right":177,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":164,"left":0,"right":163,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":163,"left":1,"right